# Simple Stripe Checkout Integration Guide

This guide explains how to integrate **Stripe API** into a **simple single-page website** to create a "Buy Now" button for payments. It is beginner-friendly and uses a minimal backend.

---

## üöÄ Features

- Accept payments using Stripe Checkout
- Minimal frontend (HTML + JS)
- Backend to create Stripe Checkout sessions
- Redirects to success and cancel pages after payment

---

## üõ† Prerequisites

1. **Stripe account**: [Sign up here](https://stripe.com)  
2. **Stripe API Keys**: Found in your Stripe Dashboard ‚Üí Developers ‚Üí API keys  
   - Secret Key ‚Üí used on the backend  
   - Publishable Key ‚Üí used on the frontend (if using Stripe Elements)  
3. **A server/backend environment**: Could be Node.js, ASP.NET Core, PHP, Python, etc.  
4. **Basic HTML/JS knowledge**  

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Basic Flow of Stripe Checkout

1. User clicks **Buy Now** on your webpage.  
2. Browser calls your backend (e.g., `/create-checkout-session`) to create a **Checkout Session**.  
3. Backend uses **Stripe Secret Key** to call the Stripe API and create a session:  
   - Define product name, price, currency, and quantity  
   - Set success/cancel URLs  
4. Stripe returns a **session URL**.  
5. Frontend redirects the user to the Stripe-hosted checkout page.  
6. After payment, user is redirected back to success or cancel page.

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Frontend Implementation (HTML + JS)

Example of a minimal HTML page:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Buy Now</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>My Product</h1>
    <p>Price: $19.99</p>

    <button id="buyBtn">Buy Now</button>

    <script>
        document.getElementById("buyBtn").onclick = () => {
            fetch("/create-checkout-session", { method: "POST" })
            .then(res => res.json())
            .then(data => {
                // Redirect to Stripe Checkout
                window.location.href = data.url;
            });
        };
    </script>
</body>
</html>
